The paper deals with the analysis of algorithms and data structures, which is a common theme in the sub-categories of cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The peeling process on a random hypergraph is a graph-theoretic concept, which is also covered in cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of stashes in hashing applications is related to the sub-category of cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), which deals with the design and analysis of numerical algorithms.
